How to set up a reoccuring task in Windows Task Scheduler:

  1. In the Windows Search bar, find Task Scheduler and lanch the application
  2. Click 'Create Task'
    a. General Tab - Name the task 
                   - Change the security option to 'Run whether user is logged on or not' 
    b. Triggers Tab > New - Set the frequency
                          - Chose a date and time to start the task 
    c. Actions Tab > New - Select 'Start a Program'
                         - Select 'Browse' to navigate to your compiled AutoIt script (ending in .exe)

    d. Leave all other settings to default


**To compile the AutoIt script, right-click the file and select 'Compile Script (x86)'
